Report Type Reference

The report type you choose determines which records and fields appear in your report. There are two kinds of report types: standard report types and custom report types.

Standard report types give access to most Salesforce data, while custom report types provide access to custom objects or views of standard objects configured by the administrator.

Salesforce provides a rich collection of standard report types that can be tailored to unique requirements.

Some Salesforce features come with pre-designed custom report types for specific use cases.
